# HTML Structure Rules

## Document Structure
- Use semantic HTML5 elements (`<header>`, `<main>`, `<nav>`, `<footer>`)
- Include proper meta tags for viewport and SEO
- Link to [styles.css](mdc:styles.css) and relevant JavaScript files
- Use `defer` attribute for non-critical JavaScript

## Navigation
- Consistent navigation structure across all pages
- Use `aria-current="page"` for active navigation items
- Include `aria-label` for navigation landmarks
- Maintain consistent header and footer across pages

## Accessibility
- Use proper heading hierarchy (h1, h2, h3)
- Include alt text for images
- Use `aria-live` regions for dynamic content updates
- Ensure proper color contrast and focus states

## Game Page Specific
- Canvas element with proper dimensions and styling
- Status elements for score and lives display
- Restart button for game reset functionality
- Proper labeling for screen readers

## Content Guidelines
- Keep content concise and engaging
- Use consistent tone and voice
- Include proper copyright notices in footer
- Dynamic year display using JavaScript